-- China shares jump as Bank of Communications seeks new private investors
-- By Grace Li and Donny Kwok
-- Sun Jul 27, 2014 11:07PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 28 (Reuters) - China shares jumped in mid-morning trade on Monday, with bank shares surging after Reuters reported the country's fifth-biggest bank by assets plans to seek more private investors.

At 0255 GMT, the Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> was up 2.3 percent, while The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings rose 2.7 percent. China's Bank of Communications Co Ltd (BoCom) <601328.SS> <3328.HK> plans to sell stakes to private investors under a government reform aimed at letting private capital play a bigger role in the economy, two people familiar with the matter told Reuters on Friday. [ID:nL4N0Q037S]